This paper discusses the implementation of Q-learning with Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) on FPGA for autonomous control systems onboard planetary rovers and spacecraft. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with learning algorithms and cognitive capabilities. The paper also focuses on the application of this architecture to planetary robotics, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions image processing, obstacle avoidance, and pyrotechnic operation control, which are related to augmented reality (cs.AR), system-level design and automation (cs.SY), and neural networks (cs.NE), respectively.
